/datum/reagent/fermi/astral.desc: An opalescent murky liquid that is said to distort your soul from your being.

/datum/reagent/fermi/basic_buffer.name: Strong basic buffer
/datum/reagent/fermi/basic_buffer.desc: This reagent will consume itself and move the pH of a beaker towards alkalinity when added to another.

/datum/reagent/fermi/basic_buffer/weak.name: Basic buffer
/datum/reagent/fermi/basic_buffer/weak.desc: This reagent will consume itself and move the pH of a beaker towards alkalinity when added to another.

/datum/reagent/fermi/belly_inflator.name: Belladine nectar
/datum/reagent/fermi/belly_inflator.desc: It will give you the lewdest tummy ache you've ever had

/datum/reagent/fermi/breast_enlarger.name: Succubus milk
/datum/reagent/fermi/breast_enlarger.desc: A volatile collodial mixture derived from milk that encourages mammary production via a potent estrogen mix.

/datum/reagent/fermi/butt_enlarger.name: Denbu Tincture
/datum/reagent/fermi/butt_enlarger.desc: A mixture of natural vitamins and valentines plant extract, causing butt enlargement in humanoids.

/datum/reagent/fermi/eigenstate.name: Eigenstasium
/datum/reagent/fermi/eigenstate.desc: A strange mixture formed from a controlled reaction of bluespace with plasma, that causes localised eigenstate fluxuations within the patient

/datum/reagent/fermi/enthrall.name: MKUltra
/datum/reagent/fermi/enthrall.desc: A forbidden deep red mixture that increases a person's succeptability to another's words. When taken by the creator, it will enhance the draw of their voice to those affected by it.

/datum/reagent/fermi/enthrallExplo.name: Gaseous MKUltra
/datum/reagent/fermi/enthrallExplo.desc: A deep red gas that when taken into a body, the recipient will experience a high and reduced control in their body for as long as it is in their system. Produced when MKUltra explodes.

/datum/reagent/fermi/fermiAcid.name: Acid vapour
/datum/reagent/fermi/fermiAcid.desc: Someone didn't do like an otter, and add acid to water.

/datum/reagent/fermi/fermiTest.name: Fermis Test Reagent
/datum/reagent/fermi/fermiTest.desc: You should be really careful with this...! Also, how did you get this?

/datum/reagent/fermi/hatmium.name: Hat growth serium
/datum/reagent/fermi/hatmium.desc: A strange substance that draws in a hat from the hat dimention.

/datum/reagent/fermi/nanite_b_gone.name: Nanite bane
/datum/reagent/fermi/nanite_b_gone.desc: A stablised EMP that is highly volatile, shocking small nano machines that will kill them off at a rapid rate in a patient's system.

/datum/reagent/fermi/nanite_b_goneTox.name: Electromagnetic crystals
/datum/reagent/fermi/nanite_b_goneTox.desc: Causes items upon the patient to sometimes short out, as well as causing a shock in the patient, if the residual charge between the crystals builds up to sufficient quantities

/datum/reagent/fermi/penis_enlarger.name: Incubus draft
/datum/reagent/fermi/penis_enlarger.desc: A volatile collodial mixture derived from various masculine solutions that encourages a larger gentleman's package via a potent testosterone mix, formula derived from a collaboration from Fermichem  and Doctor Ronald Hyatt, who is well known for his phallus palace.

/datum/reagent/fermi/plushmium.name: Plushmium
/datum/reagent/fermi/plushmium.desc: A strange chemical, seeming almost fluffy, if it were not for it being a liquid. Known to have a strange effect on plushies.

/datum/reagent/fermi/secretcatchem.name: secretcatchem
/datum/reagent/fermi/secretcatchem.desc: An illegal and hidden chem that turns people into cats. It's said that it's so rare and unstable that having it means you've been blessed. If used on someone in crit, it will turn them into a cat permanently, until the cat is killed.

/datum/reagent/fermi/yamerol.name: Yamerol
/datum/reagent/fermi/yamerol.desc: For when you've trouble speaking or breathing, just yell YAMEROL! A chem that helps soothe any congestion problems and at high concentrations restores damaged lungs and tongues!

/datum/reagent/fermi/zeolites.name: Artificial Zeolite
/datum/reagent/fermi/zeolites.desc: Lab made Zeolite, used to clear radiation from people and items alike! Splashing just a small amount(5u) onto any item can clear away large amounts of contamination, as long as its purity is at least 0.7.

/datum/reagent/firefighting_foam.name: Firefighting Foam
/datum/reagent/firefighting_foam.desc: A historical fire suppressant. Originally believed to simply displace oxygen to starve fires, it actually interferes with the combustion reaction itself. Vastly superior to the cheap water-based extinguishers found on NT vessels.

/datum/reagent/flightpotion.name: Flight Potion
/datum/reagent/flightpotion.desc: Strange mutagenic compound of unknown origins.

/datum/reagent/fluorine.name: Fluorine
/datum/reagent/fluorine.desc: A comically-reactive chemical element. The universe does not want this stuff to exist in this form in the slightest.

/datum/reagent/fluorosurfactant.name: Fluorosurfactant
/datum/reagent/fluorosurfactant.desc: A perfluoronated sulfonic acid that forms a foam when mixed with water.

/datum/reagent/foaming_agent.name: Foaming agent
/datum/reagent/foaming_agent.desc: An agent that yields metallic foam when mixed with light metal and a strong acid.

/datum/reagent/fuel/holyoil.name: Zelus Oil
/datum/reagent/fuel/holyoil.desc: Oil blessed by a greater being.

/datum/reagent/fuel/unholywater.name: Unholy Water
/datum/reagent/fuel/unholywater.desc: Something that shouldn't exist on this plane of existence.

/datum/reagent/glitter.name: generic glitter
/datum/reagent/glitter.desc: if you can see this description, contact a coder.

/datum/reagent/gluttonytoxin.name: Gluttony's Blessing
/datum/reagent/gluttonytoxin.desc: An advanced corruptive toxin produced by something terrible.

/datum/reagent/glycerol.name: Glycerol
/datum/reagent/glycerol.desc: Glycerol is a simple polyol compound. Glycerol is sweet-tasting and of low toxicity.

/datum/reagent/gold.name: Gold
/datum/reagent/gold.desc: Gold is a dense, soft, shiny metal and the most malleable and ductile metal known.

/datum/reagent/gravitum.name: Gravitum
/datum/reagent/gravitum.desc: A rare kind of null fluid, capable of temporalily removing all weight of whatever it touches.

/datum/reagent/green_ichor.name: Green Ichor
/datum/reagent/green_ichor.desc: An unknown green liquid, linked to healing of most internal wounds.

/datum/reagent/growthchem.name: Prospacillin
/datum/reagent/growthchem.desc: A stabilized altercation of size-altering liquids, this one appears to increase cell volume.

/datum/reagent/growthserum.name: Growth Serum
/datum/reagent/growthserum.desc: A commercial chemical designed to help older men in the bedroom.

/datum/reagent/hair_dye.name: Quantum Hair Dye
/datum/reagent/hair_dye.desc: Has a high chance of making you look like a mad scientist.

/datum/reagent/hairball.name: Hairball
/datum/reagent/hairball.desc: A bundle of keratinous bits and fibers, not easily digestible.

/datum/reagent/hydrogen.name: Hydrogen
/datum/reagent/hydrogen.desc: A colorless, odorless, nonmetallic, tasteless, highly combustible diatomic gas.

/datum/reagent/impedrezene.name: Impedrezene
/datum/reagent/impedrezene.desc: Impedrezene is a narcotic that impedes one's ability by slowing down the higher brain cell functions.

/datum/reagent/impure/SDGFtox.name: Synthetic-derived apoptosis factor
/datum/reagent/impure/SDGFtox.desc: Impure synthetic-derived growth factor causes certain cells to undergo cell death, causing clone damage, and damaging blood cells.

/datum/reagent/impure/SDZF.name: synthetic-derived zombie factor
/datum/reagent/impure/SDZF.desc: A horribly peverse mass of Embryonic stem cells made real by the hands of a failed chemist. Emulates normal synthetic-derived growth factor, but produces a hostile zombie at the end of it.

/datum/reagent/impure/fermiTox.name: Chemical Isomers
/datum/reagent/impure/fermiTox.desc: Toxic chemical isomers made from impure reactions. At low volumes will cause light toxin damage, but as the volume increases, it deals larger amounts, damages the liver, then eventually the heart. This is default impure chem for all chems, and changes only if stated.

/datum/reagent/impure/helgrasp.name: Helgrasp
/datum/reagent/impure/helgrasp.desc: This rare and forbidden concoction is thought to bring you closer to the grasp of the Norse goddess Hel.

/datum/reagent/impure/yamerol_tox.name: Yamer oh no
/datum/reagent/impure/yamerol_tox.desc: A dangerous, cloying toxin that stucks to a patient’s respiratory system, damaging their tongue, lungs and causing suffocation.

/datum/reagent/iodine.name: Iodine
/datum/reagent/iodine.desc: Commonly added to table salt as a nutrient. On its own it tastes far less pleasing.

/datum/reagent/liquid_dark_matter.desc: Sucks everything into the detonation point.

/datum/reagent/liquidgibs.desc: You don't even want to think about what's in here.

/datum/reagent/liquidgibs/oil.desc: You don't even want to think about what's in here.

/datum/reagent/liquidgibs/slime.desc: You don't even want to think about what's in here.

/datum/reagent/liquidgibs/synth.desc: You don't even want to think about what's in here.

/datum/reagent/liquidgibs/xeno.name: Liquid xeno gibs
/datum/reagent/liquidgibs/xeno.desc: You don't even want to think about what's in here.

/datum/reagent/lithium.name: Lithium
/datum/reagent/lithium.desc: A silver metal, its claim to fame is its remarkably low density. Using it is a bit too effective in calming oneself down.

/datum/reagent/lube.name: Space Lube
/datum/reagent/lube.desc: Lubricant is a substance introduced between two moving surfaces to reduce the friction and wear between them. giggity.

/datum/reagent/lube/superlube.name: Super Duper Lube
/datum/reagent/lube/superlube.desc: This \[REDACTED\] has been outlawed after the incident on \[DATA EXPUNGED\].

/datum/reagent/lye.name: Lye
/datum/reagent/lye.desc: Also known as sodium hydroxide. As a profession making this is somewhat underwhelming.

/datum/reagent/magillitis.name: Magillitis
/datum/reagent/magillitis.desc: An experimental serum which causes rapid muscular growth in Hominidae. Side-affects may include hypertrichosis, violent outbursts, and an unending affinity for bananas.

/datum/reagent/medicine/adminordrazine.name: Adminordrazine
/datum/reagent/medicine/adminordrazine.desc: It's magic. We don't have to explain it.

/datum/reagent/medicine/adminordrazine/q.name: Quantum Medicine
/datum/reagent/medicine/adminordrazine/q.desc: Rare and experimental particles, that apparently swap the user's body with one from an alternate dimension where it's completely healthy.

/datum/reagent/medicine/antihol.name: Antihol
/datum/reagent/medicine/antihol.desc: Purges alcoholic substance from the patient's body and eliminates its side effects.

/datum/reagent/medicine/antitoxin.name: Anti-Toxin
/datum/reagent/medicine/antitoxin.desc: Heals toxin damage and removes toxins in the bloodstream. Overdose causes toxin damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/atropine.name: Atropine
/datum/reagent/medicine/atropine.desc: If a patient is in critical condition, rapidly heals all damage types as well as regulating oxygen in the body. Excellent for stabilizing wounded patients.

/datum/reagent/medicine/bicaridine.name: Bicaridine
/datum/reagent/medicine/bicaridine.desc: Restores bruising. Overdose causes it instead.

/datum/reagent/medicine/calomel.name: Calomel
/datum/reagent/medicine/calomel.desc: Quickly purges the body of all chemicals. Toxin damage is dealt if the patient is in good condition.

/datum/reagent/medicine/changelingadrena.name: Changeling Adrenaline
/datum/reagent/medicine/changelingadrena.desc: Reduces the duration of unconciousness, knockdown and stuns. Restores stamina, but deals toxin damage when overdosed.

/datum/reagent/medicine/charcoal.name: Charcoal
/datum/reagent/medicine/charcoal.desc: Heals toxin damage as well as slowly removing any other chemicals the patient has in their bloodstream.

/datum/reagent/medicine/clonexadone.name: Clonexadone
/datum/reagent/medicine/clonexadone.desc: A chemical that derives from Cryoxadone. It specializes in healing clone damage, but nothing else. Requires very cold temperatures to properly metabolize, and metabolizes quicker than cryoxadone.

/datum/reagent/medicine/coagulant.name: Sanguirite
/datum/reagent/medicine/coagulant.desc: A proprietary coagulant used to help bleeding wounds clot faster.

/datum/reagent/medicine/coagulant/weak.name: Synthi-Sanguirite
/datum/reagent/medicine/coagulant/weak.desc: A synthetic coagulant used to help bleeding wounds clot faster. Not quite as effective as name brand Sanguirite, especially on patients with lots of cuts.

/datum/reagent/medicine/corazone.name: Corazone
/datum/reagent/medicine/corazone.desc: A medication used to treat pain, fever, and inflammation, along with heart attacks.

/datum/reagent/medicine/cryoxadone.name: Cryoxadone
/datum/reagent/medicine/cryoxadone.desc: A chemical mixture with almost magical healing powers. Its main limitation is that the patient's body temperature must be under 270K for it to metabolise correctly.

/datum/reagent/medicine/dexalin.name: Dexalin
/datum/reagent/medicine/dexalin.desc: Restores oxygen loss. Overdose causes it instead.

/datum/reagent/medicine/diphenhydramine.name: Diphenhydramine
/datum/reagent/medicine/diphenhydramine.desc: Rapidly purges the body of Histamine and reduces jitteriness. Slight chance of causing drowsiness.

/datum/reagent/medicine/earthsblood.name: Earthsblood
/datum/reagent/medicine/earthsblood.desc: Ichor from an extremely powerful plant. Great for restoring wounds, but it's a little heavy on the brain.

/datum/reagent/medicine/ephedrine.name: Ephedrine
/datum/reagent/medicine/ephedrine.desc: Increases stun resistance. Overdose deals toxin damage and inhibits breathing.

/datum/reagent/medicine/epinephrine.name: Epinephrine
/datum/reagent/medicine/epinephrine.desc: Minor boost to stun resistance. Slowly heals damage if a patient is in critical condition, as well as regulating oxygen loss. Overdose causes weakness and toxin damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/haloperidol.name: Haloperidol
/datum/reagent/medicine/haloperidol.desc: Increases depletion rates for most stimulating/hallucinogenic drugs. Reduces druggy effects and jitteriness. Severe stamina regeneration penalty, causes drowsiness. Small chance of brain damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/inacusiate.name: Inacusiate
/datum/reagent/medicine/inacusiate.desc: Instantly restores all hearing to the patient, but does not cure deafness.

/datum/reagent/medicine/inaprovaline.name: Inaprovaline
/datum/reagent/medicine/inaprovaline.desc: Stabilizes the breathing of patients. Good for those in critical condition.

/datum/reagent/medicine/kelotane.name: Kelotane
/datum/reagent/medicine/kelotane.desc: Restores fire damage. Overdose causes it instead.

/datum/reagent/medicine/lavaland_extract.name: Lavaland Extract
/datum/reagent/medicine/lavaland_extract.desc: An extract of lavaland atmospheric and mineral elements. Heals the user in small doses, but is extremely toxic otherwise.

/datum/reagent/medicine/leporazine.name: Leporazine
/datum/reagent/medicine/leporazine.desc: Leporazine will effectively regulate a patient's body temperature, ensuring it never leaves safe levels.

/datum/reagent/medicine/lesser_syndicate.name: Regenerative Nanites
/datum/reagent/medicine/lesser_syndicate.desc: Miniature medical robots that restore damage and get operatives back in the fight.

/datum/reagent/medicine/limb_regrowth.name: Carcinisoprojection Jelly
/datum/reagent/medicine/limb_regrowth.desc: Also known as \"limb regrowth jelly\", this crabby looking xenobiological jelly will rapidly regrow any missing limbs someone has at the cost of some of their blood. Do not overdose.

/datum/reagent/medicine/liquid_wisdom.name: liquid wisdom
/datum/reagent/medicine/liquid_wisdom.desc: the physical representation of wisdom, in liquid form

/datum/reagent/medicine/mine_salve.name: Miner's Salve
/datum/reagent/medicine/mine_salve.desc: A powerful painkiller. Restores bruising and burns in addition to making the patient believe they are fully healed. Also great for treating severe burn wounds in a pinch.

/datum/reagent/medicine/modafinil.name: Modafinil
/datum/reagent/medicine/modafinil.desc: Long-lasting sleep suppressant that very slightly reduces stun and knockdown times. Overdosing has horrendous side effects and deals lethal oxygen damage, will knock you unconscious if not dealt with.

/datum/reagent/medicine/morphine.name: Morphine
/datum/reagent/medicine/morphine.desc: A painkiller that allows the patient to move at full speed even in bulky objects. Causes drowsiness and eventually unconsciousness in high doses. Overdose will cause a variety of effects, ranging from minor to lethal.

/datum/reagent/medicine/muscle_stimulant.name: Muscle Stimulant
/datum/reagent/medicine/muscle_stimulant.desc: A potent chemical that allows someone under its influence to be at full physical ability even when under massive amounts of pain.

/datum/reagent/medicine/mutadone.name: Mutadone
/datum/reagent/medicine/mutadone.desc: Removes jitteriness and restores genetic defects.

/datum/reagent/medicine/neo_jelly.name: Neo Jelly
/datum/reagent/medicine/neo_jelly.desc: Gradually regenerates all types of damage, without harming slime anatomy. Can overdose.

/datum/reagent/medicine/neurine.name: Neurine
/datum/reagent/medicine/neurine.desc: Reacts with neural tissue, helping reform damaged connections. Can cure minor traumas.

/datum/reagent/medicine/oculine.name: Oculine
/datum/reagent/medicine/oculine.desc: Quickly restores eye damage, cures nearsightedness, and has a chance to restore vision to the blind.

/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine.name: Omnizine
/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine.desc: Slowly heals all damage types. Overdose will cause damage in all types instead.

/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine/godbloo.name: Godblood
/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine/godbloo.desc: Slowly heals all damage types. Has a rather high overdose threshold. Glows with mysterious power.

/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine/protozi.name: Protozine
/datum/reagent/medicine/omnizine/protozi.desc: A less environmentally friendly and somewhat weaker variant of omnizine.

/datum/reagent/medicine/oxandrolone.name: Oxandrolone
/datum/reagent/medicine/oxandrolone.desc: Stimulates the healing of severe burns. Extremely rapidly heals severe burns and slowly heals minor ones. Overdose will worsen existing burns.

/datum/reagent/medicine/pen_acid.name: Pentetic Acid
/datum/reagent/medicine/pen_acid.desc: Reduces massive amounts of radiation and toxin damage while purging other chemicals from the body.

/datum/reagent/medicine/pen_acid/pen_jel.name: Pentetic Jelly
/datum/reagent/medicine/pen_acid/pen_jel.desc: Reduces massive amounts of radiation and toxin damage while purging other chemicals from the body. Slimepeople friendly!

/datum/reagent/medicine/perfluorodecalin.name: Perfluorodecalin
/datum/reagent/medicine/perfluorodecalin.desc: Extremely rapidly restores breathing deprivation, but inhibits speech. May also heal small amounts of bruising and burns.

/datum/reagent/medicine/polypyr.name: Polypyrylium Oligomers
/datum/reagent/medicine/polypyr.desc: A purple mixture of short polyelectrolyte chains not easily synthesized in the laboratory. It is valued as an intermediate in the synthesis of the cutting edge pharmaceuticals.

/datum/reagent/medicine/psicodine.name: Psicodine
/datum/reagent/medicine/psicodine.desc: Suppresses anxiety and other various forms of mental distress. Overdose causes hallucinations and minor toxin damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/pyroxadone.name: Pyroxadone
/datum/reagent/medicine/pyroxadone.desc: A mixture of cryoxadone and slime jelly, that apparently inverses the requirement for its activation.

/datum/reagent/medicine/regen_jelly.name: Regenerative Jelly
/datum/reagent/medicine/regen_jelly.desc: Gradually regenerates all types of damage, without harming slime anatomy.

/datum/reagent/medicine/rezadone.name: Rezadone
/datum/reagent/medicine/rezadone.desc: A powder derived from fish toxin, Rezadone can effectively treat genetic damage as well as restoring minor wounds. Overdose will cause intense nausea and minor toxin damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/sal_acid.name: Salicylic Acid
/datum/reagent/medicine/sal_acid.desc: Stimulates the healing of severe bruises. Extremely rapidly heals severe bruising and slowly heals minor ones. Overdose will worsen existing bruising.

/datum/reagent/medicine/salbutamol.name: Salbutamol
/datum/reagent/medicine/salbutamol.desc: Rapidly restores breathing deprivation as well as preventing more of it to an extent. Causes jittering.

/datum/reagent/medicine/salglu_solution.name: Saline-Glucose Solution
/datum/reagent/medicine/salglu_solution.desc: Has a 33% chance per metabolism cycle to heal brute and burn damage. Can be used as a temporary blood substitute, as well as slowly speeding blood regeneration.

/datum/reagent/medicine/silibinin.name: Silibinin
/datum/reagent/medicine/silibinin.desc: A thistle derrived hepatoprotective flavolignan mixture that help reverse damage to the liver.

/datum/reagent/medicine/silver_sulfadiaz.name: Silver Sulfadiazine
/datum/reagent/medicine/silver_sulfadiaz.desc: If used in touch-based applications, immediately restores burn wounds as well as restoring more over time. It is mildly poisonous taken orally or by injection. If overdosed, deals brute and minor liver damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/spaceacillin.name: Spaceacillin
/datum/reagent/medicine/spaceacillin.desc: Spaceacillin will prevent a patient from conventionally spreading any diseases they are currently infected with. Also reduces infection in serious burns.

/datum/reagent/medicine/stimulants.name: Stimulants
/datum/reagent/medicine/stimulants.desc: Increases stun resistance and movement speed in addition to restoring minor damage and weakness. Overdose causes weakness and toxin damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/strange_reagent.name: Strange Reagent
/datum/reagent/medicine/strange_reagent.desc: A miracle drug capable of bringing the dead back to life. Only functions when applied by patch or spray, if the target has less than 100 brute and burn damage (independent of one another) and hasn't been husked. Causes slight damage to the living.

/datum/reagent/medicine/styptic_powder.name: Styptic Powder
/datum/reagent/medicine/styptic_powder.desc: If used in touch-based applications, immediately restores bruising as well as restoring more over time. It is poisonous if taken orally or by injection. If overdosed, deals brute and minor liver damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/synaphydramine.name: Diphen-Synaptizine
/datum/reagent/medicine/synaphydramine.desc: Reduces drowsiness, hallucinations, and Histamine from body.

/datum/reagent/medicine/synaptizine.name: Synaptizine
/datum/reagent/medicine/synaptizine.desc: Increases resistance to stuns as well as reducing drowsiness and hallucinations.

/datum/reagent/medicine/synaptizine/syna.name: virus rations
/datum/reagent/medicine/synaptizine/syna.desc: Increases resistance to stuns as well as reducing drowsiness and hallucinations.

/datum/reagent/medicine/syndicate_nanite.name: Restorative Nanites
/datum/reagent/medicine/syndicate_nanite.desc: Miniature medical robots that swiftly restore bodily damage.

/datum/reagent/medicine/synthblood_delux.name: Super-pressurized hydraulic liquid
/datum/reagent/medicine/synthblood_delux.desc: Сверхэффективная гидравлическая жидкость, способная быстро восстановить работоспособность системы охлаждения у синтетиков. Была изобретена и применяется CyberSun для ремонта своих боевых роботов на передовой. Процесс производства достаточно дорогостоящий и требует применения блюспейс-сжатия, атомизации и насыщения. Более простые варианты данной жидкости могут быть произведены с помощью лишь блюспейс-сжатия и могут превращаться в обычную гидравлическую жидкость в соотношении 1/10. Вызывает кратковременные сбои сенсоров при применении.

/datum/reagent/medicine/synthflesh.name: Synthflesh
/datum/reagent/medicine/synthflesh.desc: Has a 100% chance of healing large amounts of brute and burn damage very quickly. One unit of the chemical will heal one point of damage. Touch application only.

/datum/reagent/medicine/system_cleaner.name: System Cleaner
/datum/reagent/medicine/system_cleaner.desc: A reagent with special properties causing it to slowly reduce corruption in robots. Mildly toxic for organics.

/datum/reagent/medicine/tricordrazine.name: Tricordrazine
/datum/reagent/medicine/tricordrazine.desc: Has a high chance to heal all types of damage. Overdose instead causes it.

/datum/reagent/mercury.name: Mercury
/datum/reagent/mercury.desc: A curious metal that's a liquid at room temperature. Neurodegenerative and very bad for the mind.

/datum/reagent/metalgen.name: Metalgen
/datum/reagent/metalgen.desc: A purple metal morphic liquid, said to impose it's metallic properties on whatever it touches.

/datum/reagent/moonsugar.name: Moon Sugar
/datum/reagent/moonsugar.desc: The primary precursor for an ancient feline delicacy known as skooma. While it has no notable effects on it's own, mixing it with morphine in a chilled container may yield interesting results.

/datum/reagent/mulligan.name: Mulligan Toxin
/datum/reagent/mulligan.desc: This toxin will rapidly change the DNA of human beings. Commonly used by Syndicate spies and assassins in need of an emergency ID change.

/datum/reagent/mustardgrind.name: Mustardgrind
/datum/reagent/mustardgrind.desc: A powerd that is mixed with water and enzymes to make mustard.

/datum/reagent/nitrogen.name: Nitrogen
/datum/reagent/nitrogen.desc: A colorless, odorless, tasteless gas. A simple asphyxiant that can silently displace vital oxygen.

/datum/reagent/nitroglycerin.name: Nitroglycerin
/datum/reagent/nitroglycerin.desc: Nitroglycerin is a heavy, colorless, oily, explosive liquid obtained by nitrating glycerol.

/datum/reagent/nitrous_oxide.name: Nitrous Oxide
/datum/reagent/nitrous_oxide.desc: A potent oxidizer used as fuel in rockets and as an anaesthetic during surgery.

/datum/reagent/nitryl.name: Nitryl
/datum/reagent/nitryl.desc: A highly reactive gas that makes you feel faster

/datum/reagent/oil.name: Oil
/datum/reagent/oil.desc: Burns in a small smoky fire, mostly used to get Ash.

/datum/reagent/oxygen.name: Oxygen
/datum/reagent/oxygen.desc: A colorless, odorless gas. Grows on trees but is still pretty valuable.

/datum/reagent/pax.name: pax
/datum/reagent/pax.desc: A colorless liquid that suppresses violence on the subjects.

/datum/reagent/pax/catnip.name: catnip
/datum/reagent/pax/catnip.desc: A colorless liquid that makes people more peaceful and felines more happy.

/datum/reagent/pax/peaceborg.name: synth-pax
/datum/reagent/pax/peaceborg.desc: A colorless liquid that suppresses violence on the subjects. Cheaper to synthetize, but wears out faster than normal Pax.

/datum/reagent/peaceborg_confuse.name: Dizzying Solution
/datum/reagent/peaceborg_confuse.desc: Makes the target off balance and dizzy

/datum/reagent/peaceborg_tire.name: Tiring Solution
/datum/reagent/peaceborg_tire.desc: An extremely weak stamina-toxin that tires out the target. Completely harmless.

/datum/reagent/phenol.name: Phenol
/datum/reagent/phenol.desc: An aromatic ring of carbon with a hydroxyl group. A useful precursor to some medicines, but has no healing properties on its own.

/datum/reagent/phlogiston.name: Phlogiston
/datum/reagent/phlogiston.desc: Catches you on fire and makes you ignite.

/datum/reagent/phosphorus.name: Phosphorus
/datum/reagent/phosphorus.desc: A ruddy red powder that burns readily. Though it comes in many colors, the general theme is always the same.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment.name: Generic nutriment
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment.desc: Some kind of nutriment. You can't really tell what it is. You should probably report it, along with how you obtained it.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/endurogrow.name: Enduro Grow
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/endurogrow.desc: A specialized nutriment, which decreases product quantity and potency, but strengthens the plants endurance.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/eznutrimen.name: E-Z-Nutrient
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/eznutrimen.desc: Contains electrolytes. It's what plants crave.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/left4zednu.name: Left 4 Zed
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/left4zednu.desc: Unstable nutriment that makes plants mutate more often than usual.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/liquideart.name: Liquid Earthquake
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/liquideart.desc: A specialized nutriment, which increases the plant's production speed, as well as it's susceptibility to weeds.

/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/robustharv.name: Robust Harvest
/datum/reagent/plantnutriment/robustharv.desc: Very potent nutriment that slows plants from mutating.

/datum/reagent/plastic_polymers.name: plastic polymers
/datum/reagent/plastic_polymers.desc: the petroleum based components of plastic.

/datum/reagent/potassium.name: Potassium
/datum/reagent/potassium.desc: A soft, low-melting solid that can easily be cut with a knife. Reacts violently with water.

/datum/reagent/preservahyde.name: Preservahyde
/datum/reagent/preservahyde.desc: A powerful preservation agent, utilizing the preservative effects of formaldehyde with significantly less of the histamine.

/datum/reagent/pyrosium.name: Pyrosium
/datum/reagent/pyrosium.desc: Comes into existence at 20K. As long as there is sufficient oxygen for it to react with, Pyrosium slowly heats all other reagents in the container.

/datum/reagent/radium.name: Radium
/datum/reagent/radium.desc: Radium is an alkaline earth metal. It is extremely radioactive.

/datum/reagent/red_ichor.name: Red Ichor
/datum/reagent/red_ichor.desc: An unknown red liquid, linked to healing of most moral wounds.

/datum/reagent/romerol.name: Romerol
/datum/reagent/romerol.desc: Romerol is a highly experimental bioterror agent which causes dormant nodules to be etched into the grey matter of the subject. These nodules only become active upon death of the host, upon which, the secondary structures activate and take control of the host body.

/datum/reagent/royal_bee_jelly.name: royal bee jelly
/datum/reagent/royal_bee_jelly.desc: Royal Bee Jelly, if injected into a Queen Space Bee said bee will split into two bees.

/datum/reagent/sandparasite.name: Sand parasite
/datum/reagent/sandparasite.desc: Миллионы маленьких паразитов готовых съесть любую органику, до которой смогут добраться.

/datum/reagent/serotrotium.name: Serotrotium
/datum/reagent/serotrotium.desc: A chemical compound that promotes concentrated production of the serotonin neurotransmitter in humans.

/datum/reagent/shrinkchem.name: Diminicillin
/datum/reagent/shrinkchem.desc: A stabilized altercation of size-altering liquids, this one appears to decrease cell volume.

/datum/reagent/silicon.name: Silicon
/datum/reagent/silicon.desc: A tetravalent metalloid, silicon is less reactive than its chemical analog carbon.

/datum/reagent/silver.name: Silver
/datum/reagent/silver.desc: A soft, white, lustrous transition metal, it has the highest electrical conductivity of any element and the highest thermal conductivity of any metal.

/datum/reagent/sizechem.name: Cell-Volume Altering Base
/datum/reagent/sizechem.desc: A stabilized compound liquid, used as a basis for increasing or decreasing the size of living matter with more recipes.

/datum/reagent/slime_toxin.name: Slime Mutation Toxin
/datum/reagent/slime_toxin.desc: A toxin that turns organic material into slime.

/datum/reagent/smart_foaming_agent.name: Smart foaming agent
/datum/reagent/smart_foaming_agent.desc: An agent that yields metallic foam which conforms to area boundaries when mixed with light metal and a strong acid.

/datum/reagent/smoke_powder.name: Smoke Powder
/datum/reagent/smoke_powder.desc: Makes a large cloud of smoke that can carry reagents.

/datum/reagent/sodium.name: Sodium
/datum/reagent/sodium.desc: A soft silver metal that can easily be cut with a knife. It's not salt just yet, so refrain from putting in on your chips.

/datum/reagent/sorium.name: Sorium
/datum/reagent/sorium.desc: Sends everything flying from the detonation point.

/datum/reagent/space_cleaner.name: Space cleaner
/datum/reagent/space_cleaner.desc: A compound used to clean things. Now with 50% more sodium hypochlorite!

/datum/reagent/space_cleaner/ez_clean.name: EZ Clean
/datum/reagent/space_cleaner/ez_clean.desc: A powerful, acidic cleaner sold by Waffle Co. Affects organic matter while leaving other objects unaffected.

/datum/reagent/space_cleaner/sterilizine.name: Sterilizine
/datum/reagent/space_cleaner/sterilizine.desc: Sterilizes wounds in preparation for surgery.

/datum/reagent/spraytan.name: Spray Tan
/datum/reagent/spraytan.desc: A substance applied to the skin to darken the skin.

/datum/reagent/stabilizing_agent.name: Stabilizing Agent
/datum/reagent/stabilizing_agent.desc: Keeps unstable chemicals stable. This does not work on everything.

/datum/reagent/stable_plasma.name: Stable Plasma
/datum/reagent/stable_plasma.desc: Non-flammable plasma locked into a liquid form that cannot ignite or become gaseous/solid.

/datum/reagent/stimulum.name: Stimulum
/datum/reagent/stimulum.desc: An unstable experimental gas that greatly increases the energy of those that inhale it

/datum/reagent/sulfur.name: Sulfur
/datum/reagent/sulfur.desc: A sickly yellow solid mostly known for its nasty smell. It's actually much more helpful than it looks in biochemisty.

/datum/reagent/syndicateadrenals.name: Syndicate Adrenaline
/datum/reagent/syndicateadrenals.desc: Regenerates your stamina and increases your reaction time.

/datum/reagent/synthtissue.name: Synthtissue
/datum/reagent/synthtissue.desc: Synthetic tissue used for grafting onto damaged organs during surgery, or for treating limb damage. Has a very tight growth window between 305-320, any higher and the temperature will cause the cells to die. Additionally, growth time is considerably long, so chemists are encouraged to leave beakers with said reaction ongoing, while they tend to their other duties.

/datum/reagent/telecrystal.name: Credits Dust
/datum/reagent/telecrystal.desc: A yellow dust comprised of something that was much more useful when it was intact.

/datum/reagent/terror_black_toxin.name: Black Terror venom
/datum/reagent/terror_black_toxin.desc: An incredibly toxic venom injected by the Black Widow spider.

/datum/reagent/terror_eggs.name: terror spider eggs
/datum/reagent/terror_eggs.desc: An incredibly toxic venom that spreads infestation.

/datum/reagent/teslium.name: Teslium
/datum/reagent/teslium.desc: An unstable, electrically-charged metallic slurry. Periodically electrocutes its victim, and makes electrocutions against them more deadly. Excessively heating teslium results in dangerous destabilization. Do not allow to come into contact with water.

/datum/reagent/teslium/energized_jelly.name: Energized Jelly
/datum/reagent/teslium/energized_jelly.desc: Electrically-charged jelly. Boosts jellypeople's nervous system, but only shocks other lifeforms.

/datum/reagent/thermite.name: Thermite
/datum/reagent/thermite.desc: Thermite produces an aluminothermic reaction known as a thermite reaction. Can be used to melt walls.

/datum/reagent/toxin/acid.name: Sulphuric acid
/datum/reagent/toxin/acid.desc: A strong mineral acid with the molecular formula H2SO4.

/datum/reagent/toxin/acid/fluacid.name: Fluorosulfuric acid
/datum/reagent/toxin/acid/fluacid.desc: Fluorosulfuric acid is an extremely corrosive chemical substance.

/datum/reagent/toxin/amanitin.name: Amanitin
/datum/reagent/toxin/amanitin.desc: A very powerful delayed toxin. Upon full metabolization, a massive amount of toxin damage will be dealt depending on how long it has been in the victim's bloodstream.

/datum/reagent/toxin/amatoxin.name: Amatoxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/amatoxin.desc: A powerful poison derived from certain species of mushroom.

/datum/reagent/toxin/anacea.name: Anacea
/datum/reagent/toxin/anacea.desc: A toxin that quickly purges medicines and metabolizes very slowly.

/datum/reagent/toxin/bad_food.name: Bad Food
/datum/reagent/toxin/bad_food.desc: The result of some abomination of cookery, food so bad it's toxic.

/datum/reagent/toxin/bonehurtingjuice.name: Bone Hurting Juice
/datum/reagent/toxin/bonehurtingjuice.desc: A strange substance that looks a lot like water. Drinking it is oddly tempting. Oof ouch.

/datum/reagent/toxin/bungotoxin.name: Bungotoxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/bungotoxin.desc: A horrible cardiotoxin that protects the humble bungo pit.

/datum/reagent/toxin/carpotoxin.name: Carpotoxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/carpotoxin.desc: A deadly neurotoxin produced by the dreaded spess carp.

/datum/reagent/toxin/chloralhydrate.name: Chloral Hydrate
/datum/reagent/toxin/chloralhydrate.desc: A powerful sedative that induces confusion and drowsiness before putting its target to sleep.

/datum/reagent/toxin/coffeepowder.name: Coffee Grounds
/datum/reagent/toxin/coffeepowder.desc: Finely ground coffee beans, used to make coffee.

/datum/reagent/toxin/coniine.name: Coniine
/datum/reagent/toxin/coniine.desc: Coniine metabolizes extremely slowly, but deals high amounts of toxin damage and stops breathing.

/datum/reagent/toxin/curare.name: Curare
/datum/reagent/toxin/curare.desc: Causes slight toxin damage followed by chain-stunning and oxygen damage.

/datum/reagent/toxin/cyanide.name: Cyanide
/datum/reagent/toxin/cyanide.desc: An infamous poison known for its use in assassination. Causes small amounts of toxin damage with a small chance of oxygen damage or a stun.

/datum/reagent/toxin/delayed.name: Toxin Microcapsules
/datum/reagent/toxin/delayed.desc: Causes heavy toxin damage after a brief time of inactivity.

/datum/reagent/toxin/fakebeer.name: Beer
/datum/reagent/toxin/fakebeer.desc: A specially-engineered sedative disguised as beer. It induces instant sleep in its target.

/datum/reagent/toxin/fentanyl.name: Fentanyl
/datum/reagent/toxin/fentanyl.desc: Fentanyl will inhibit brain function and cause toxin damage before eventually knocking out its victim.

/datum/reagent/toxin/formaldehyde.name: Formaldehyde
/datum/reagent/toxin/formaldehyde.desc: Formaldehyde, on its own, is a fairly weak toxin. It contains trace amounts of Histamine, very rarely making it decay into Histamine.

/datum/reagent/toxin/ghoulpowder.name: Ghoul Powder
/datum/reagent/toxin/ghoulpowder.desc: A strong neurotoxin that slows metabolism to a death-like state, while keeping the patient fully active. Causes toxin buildup if used too long.

/datum/reagent/toxin/heparin.name: Heparin
/datum/reagent/toxin/heparin.desc: A powerful anticoagulant. All open cut wounds on the victim will open up and bleed much faster

/datum/reagent/toxin/histamine.name: Histamine
/datum/reagent/toxin/histamine.desc: Histamine's effects become more dangerous depending on the dosage amount. They range from mildly annoying to incredibly lethal.

/datum/reagent/toxin/initropidril.name: Initropidril
/datum/reagent/toxin/initropidril.desc: A powerful poison with insidious effects. It can cause stuns, lethal breathing failure, and cardiac arrest.

/datum/reagent/toxin/itching_powder.name: Itching Powder
/datum/reagent/toxin/itching_powder.desc: A powder that induces itching upon contact with the skin. Causes the victim to scratch at their itches and has a very low chance to decay into Histamine.

/datum/reagent/toxin/leadacetate.name: Lead Acetate
/datum/reagent/toxin/leadacetate.desc: Used hundreds of years ago as a sweetener, before it was realized that it's incredibly poisonous.

/datum/reagent/toxin/leaper_venom.name: Leaper venom
/datum/reagent/toxin/leaper_venom.desc: A toxin spat out by leapers that, while harmless in small doses, quickly creates a toxic reaction if too much is in the body.

/datum/reagent/toxin/lexorin.name: Lexorin
/datum/reagent/toxin/lexorin.desc: A powerful poison used to stop respiration.

/datum/reagent/toxin/lipolicide.name: Lipolicide
/datum/reagent/toxin/lipolicide.desc: A powerful toxin that will destroy fat cells, massively reducing body weight in a short time. Deadly to those without nutriment in their body.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mimesbane.name: Mime's Bane
/datum/reagent/toxin/mimesbane.desc: A nonlethal neurotoxin that interferes with the victim's ability to gesture.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mindbreaker.name: Mindbreaker Toxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/mindbreaker.desc: A powerful hallucinogen. Not a thing to be messed with. For some mental patients. it counteracts their symptoms and anchors them to reality.

/datum/reagent/toxin/minttoxin.name: Mint Toxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/minttoxin.desc: Useful for dealing with undesirable customers.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen.name: Unstable mutagen
/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen.desc: Might cause unpredictable mutations. Keep away from children.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen/mutagenviru.name: mutagenic agar
/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen/mutagenviru.desc: Might cause unpredictable mutations. Keep away from children.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen/mutagenviru.name: sucrose agar
/datum/reagent/toxin/mutagen/mutagenviru.desc: Might cause unpredictable mutations. Keep away from children.

/datum/reagent/toxin/mutetoxin.name: Mute Toxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/mutetoxin.desc: A nonlethal poison that inhibits speech in its victim.

/datum/reagent/toxin/pancuronium.name: Pancuronium
/datum/reagent/toxin/pancuronium.desc: An undetectable toxin that swiftly incapacitates its victim. May also cause breathing failure.

/datum/reagent/toxin/pestkiller.name: Pest Killer
/datum/reagent/toxin/pestkiller.desc: A harmful toxic mixture to kill pests. Do not ingest!

/datum/reagent/toxin/plantbgone.name: Plant-B-Gone
/datum/reagent/toxin/plantbgone.desc: A harmful toxic mixture to kill plantlife. Do not ingest!

/datum/reagent/toxin/plantbgone/weedkill.name: Weed Killer
/datum/reagent/toxin/plantbgone/weedkill.desc: A harmful toxic mixture to kill weeds. Do not ingest!

/datum/reagent/toxin/polonium.name: Polonium
/datum/reagent/toxin/polonium.desc: An extremely radioactive material in liquid form. Ingestion results in fatal irradiation.

/datum/reagent/toxin/rotatium.name: Rotatium
/datum/reagent/toxin/rotatium.desc: A constantly swirling, oddly colourful fluid. Causes the consumer's sense of direction and hand-eye coordination to become wild.

/datum/reagent/toxin/skewium.name: Skewium
/datum/reagent/toxin/skewium.desc: A strange, dull coloured liquid that appears to warp back and forth inside its container. Causes any consumer to experience a visual phenomena similar to said warping.

/datum/reagent/toxin/slimejelly.name: Slime Jelly
/datum/reagent/toxin/slimejelly.desc: A gooey semi-liquid produced from one of the deadliest lifeforms in existence. SO REAL.

/datum/reagent/toxin/sodium_thiopental.name: Sodium Thiopental
/datum/reagent/toxin/sodium_thiopental.desc: Sodium Thiopental induces heavy weakness in its target as well as unconsciousness.

/datum/reagent/toxin/spewium.name: Spewium
/datum/reagent/toxin/spewium.desc: A powerful emetic, causes uncontrollable vomiting.  May result in vomiting organs at high doses.

/datum/reagent/toxin/spore.name: Spore Toxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/spore.desc: A natural toxin produced by blob spores that inhibits vision when ingested.

/datum/reagent/toxin/spore_burning.name: Burning Spore Toxin
/datum/reagent/toxin/spore_burning.desc: A natural toxin produced by blob spores that induces combustion in its victim.

/datum/reagent/toxin/staminatoxin.name: Tirizene
/datum/reagent/toxin/staminatoxin.desc: A nonlethal poison that causes extreme fatigue and weakness in its victim.

/datum/reagent/toxin/sulfonal.name: Sulfonal
/datum/reagent/toxin/sulfonal.desc: A stealthy poison that deals minor toxin damage and eventually puts the target to sleep.

/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder.name: Ground Tea Leaves
/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder.desc: Finely shredded tea leaves, used for making tea.

/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder/green.name: Ground Green Tea Leaves
/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder/green.desc: Finely shredded tea leaves, used for making tea.

/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder/red.name: Ground Red Tea Leaves
/datum/reagent/toxin/teapowder/red.desc: Finely shredded tea leaves, used for making tea.

/datum/reagent/toxin/venom.name: Venom
/datum/reagent/toxin/venom.desc: An exotic poison extracted from highly toxic fauna. Causes scaling amounts of toxin damage and bruising depending and dosage. Often decays into Histamine.

/datum/reagent/toxin/zombiepowder.name: Zombie Powder
/datum/reagent/toxin/zombiepowder.desc: A strong neurotoxin that puts the subject into a death-like state.

/datum/reagent/tranquility.name: Tranquility
/datum/reagent/tranquility.desc: A highly mutative liquid of unknown origin.

/datum/reagent/uranium.name: Uranium
/datum/reagent/uranium.desc: A silvery-white metallic chemical element in the actinide series, weakly radioactive.

/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood.name: decaying uranium gel
/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood.desc: A silvery-white metallic chemical element in the actinide series, weakly radioactive.

/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood/.name: stable uranium gel
/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood/.desc: A silvery-white metallic chemical element in the actinide series, weakly radioactive.

/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood/.name: unstable uranium gel
/datum/reagent/uranium/uraniumvirusfood/.desc: A silvery-white metallic chemical element in the actinide series, weakly radioactive.

/datum/reagent/water.name: Water
/datum/reagent/water.desc: An ubiquitous chemical substance that is composed of hydrogen and oxygen.

/datum/reagent/water/hollowwater.name: Hollow Water
/datum/reagent/water/hollowwater.desc: An ubiquitous chemical substance that is composed of hydrogen and oxygen, but it looks kinda hollow.

/datum/reagent/water/salt.name: Saltwater
/datum/reagent/water/salt.desc: Water, but salty. Smells like... the station infirmary?

/datum/reagent/wittel.name: Wittel
/datum/reagent/wittel.desc: An extremely rare metallic-white substance only found on demon-class planets.

/datum/reagent/xenomicrobes.name: Xenomicrobes
/datum/reagent/xenomicrobes.desc: Microbes with an entirely alien cellular structure.
